---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { products } from '../../data/products';
import type { Product } from '../../data/products';

const thermostat = products.find(p => p.slug === 'emerson-sensi-touch-2')!;
const speaker = products.find(p => p.slug === 'amazon-echo-dot-5th-gen')!;
const bulb = products.find(p => p.slug === 'kasa-smart-bulb-kl135')!;
const plug = products.find(p => p.slug === 'kasa-outdoor-smart-plug-ep40a')!;
const camera = products.find(p => p.slug === 'wyze-cam-v4')!;
---

<Layout
  title="Best Smart Home Starter Kit Under $200 (2026)"
  description="How to build a complete smart home starter setup for under $200: smart thermostat, voice assistant, smart bulbs, and smart plug. Everything you need to start."
>
  <div class="bg-amber-50 border-b border-amber-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-2 text-xs text-amber-800 text-center">
      This site earns commissions from purchases made through our links at no extra cost to you.
    </div>
  </div>

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <nav class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-green-700">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">›</span>
      <a href="/smart-home" class="hover:text-green-700">Smart Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">›</span>
      Best Smart Home Starter Kit Under $200
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 leading-tight">
      Best Smart Home Starter Kit Under $200 (2026)
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">Last updated: April 2026 · Complete starter kit guide</p>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Most smart home guides send you toward pre-packaged starter kits that lock you into one brand's ecosystem and charge a premium for the bundle. This guide takes a different approach: we picked the best individual components and built the most functional $200 starter kit from scratch.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
      The result is a voice-controlled home with a smart thermostat, smart bulbs in your main living area, a smart plug for automating appliances, and an optional security camera — all on Alexa, all under $200 total.
    </p>

    <!-- Kit Summary Box -->
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-12">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">The Complete $200 Smart Home Starter Kit</p>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-sm">Emerson Sensi Smart Thermostat</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Voice-controlled HVAC scheduling, no C-wire needed</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-right flex-shrink-0">
            <p class="font-bold text-gray-900">$70</p>
            <a href={thermostat.affiliateUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" class="text-xs text-green-700 hover:underline">Amazon →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="border-t border-green-200"></div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-sm">Amazon Echo Dot (5th Gen)</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Alexa voice control hub for the whole kit</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-right flex-shrink-0">
            <p class="font-bold text-gray-900">$50</p>
            <a href={speaker.affiliateUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" class="text-xs text-green-700 hover:underline">Amazon →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="border-t border-green-200"></div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-sm">Kasa KL135 Smart Bulbs (2-pack)</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Voice-dimming and color control for your main lights</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-right flex-shrink-0">
            <p class="font-bold text-gray-900">$30</p>
            <a href={bulb.affiliateUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" class="text-xs text-green-700 hover:underline">Amazon →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="border-t border-green-200"></div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-sm">Kasa EP40 Outdoor Smart Plug</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Automate holiday lights, fans, and outdoor devices</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-right flex-shrink-0">
            <p class="font-bold text-gray-900">$17</p>
            <a href={plug.affiliateUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" class="text-xs text-green-700 hover:underline">Amazon →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="border-t border-green-200 pt-3 mt-3">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <p class="font-bold text-gray-900">Total</p>
            <p class="font-bold text-green-700 text-lg">$167</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">$33 under budget — enough to add a Wyze Cam v4 ($36) for basic security coverage</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Individual Product Breakdowns -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Each Component Explained</h2>

    <!-- Thermostat -->
    <section id="thermostat" class="mb-14 scroll-mt-20">
      <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-8 mb-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">Step 1 — Temperature Control</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-start justify-between gap-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">{thermostat.name}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">${thermostat.price} &nbsp;·&nbsp; ⭐ {thermostat.rating}/5</p>
          </div>
          <a href={thermostat.affiliateUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" class="inline-block bg-green-700 text-white px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-green-800 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap">
            Check on Amazon →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-sm">The Emerson Sensi is the starting point because it has the biggest impact on your energy bill — and at $70 with no C-wire requirement, it's the most universally installable smart thermostat available. It works with Alexa, Google Home, and SmartThings, and the battery-powered design means it works in virtually any home.</p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 text-sm">Why it makes the kit</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-700">
            {thermostat.pros.slice(0, 3).map(pro => (
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>{pro}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 text-sm">Trade-offs to know</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-700">
            {thermostat.cons.slice(0, 3).map(con => (
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 flex-shrink-0">✗</span>{con}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Echo Dot -->
    <section id="echo-dot" class="mb-14 scroll-mt-20">
      <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-8 mb-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">Step 2 — Voice Control Hub</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-start justify-between gap-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">{speaker.name}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">${speaker.price} &nbsp;·&nbsp; ⭐ {speaker.rating}/5</p>
          </div>
          <a href={speaker.affiliateUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" class="inline-block bg-green-700 text-white px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-green-800 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap">
            Check on Amazon →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-sm">The Echo Dot is the brain of this kit. "Alexa, set the thermostat to 70." "Alexa, turn off the living room lights." "Alexa, turn on the porch plug." Without a voice assistant hub, you're opening apps — with one, everything responds to voice. The 5th gen adds an eero Wi-Fi extender and a built-in temperature sensor that enables additional automations.</p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 text-sm">Why it makes the kit</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-700">
            {speaker.pros.slice(0, 3).map(pro => (
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>{pro}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 text-sm">Trade-offs to know</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-700">
            {speaker.cons.slice(0, 3).map(con => (
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 flex-shrink-0">✗</span>{con}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Smart Bulbs -->
    <section id="bulbs" class="mb-14 scroll-mt-20">
      <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-8 mb-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">Step 3 — Smart Lighting</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-start justify-between gap-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">{bulb.name}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">~$15/bulb &nbsp;·&nbsp; ⭐ {bulb.rating}/5</p>
          </div>
          <a href={bulb.affiliateUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" class="inline-block bg-green-700 text-white px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-green-800 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap">
            Check on Amazon →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-sm">Kasa KL135 is the best no-hub smart color bulb on the market. Direct Wi-Fi connection means no separate bridge — you screw them in, add them in the Kasa app (also visible in Alexa), and you're done. At $15/bulb, start with 2 in your main living area; expand room by room as budget allows.</p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 text-sm">Why it makes the kit</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-700">
            {bulb.pros.slice(0, 3).map(pro => (
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>{pro}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 text-sm">Trade-offs to know</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-700">
            {bulb.cons.slice(0, 3).map(con => (
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 flex-shrink-0">✗</span>{con}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Smart Plug -->
    <section id="plug" class="mb-14 scroll-mt-20">
      <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-8 mb-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">Step 4 — Smart Plug</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-start justify-between gap-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">{plug.name}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">${plug.price} &nbsp;·&nbsp; ⭐ {plug.rating}/5</p>
          </div>
          <a href={plug.affiliateUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" class="inline-block bg-green-700 text-white px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-green-800 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap">
            Check on Amazon →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-sm">A smart plug turns any dumb appliance into a smart one. The Kasa EP40 gets the nod over an indoor plug because the outdoor rating unlocks more use cases: holiday string lights on a schedule, a fan on a timer, a window A/C tied to Alexa. Two independently controlled outlets at $17 is exceptional value.</p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 text-sm">Why it makes the kit</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-700">
            {plug.pros.slice(0, 3).map(pro => (
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>{pro}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 text-sm">Trade-offs to know</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-700">
            {plug.cons.slice(0, 3).map(con => (
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 flex-shrink-0">✗</span>{con}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Optional camera -->
    <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-12">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Optional Add-On — Security Camera ($36)</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between gap-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">{camera.name}</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">{camera.tagline}</p>
        </div>
        <a href={camera.affiliateUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" class="inline-block border border-gray-300 text-gray-700 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap">
          Check on Amazon →
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-3 leading-relaxed">If budget allows, the Wyze Cam v4 at $36 adds 2K indoor security coverage. With free local storage (microSD card) and no mandatory subscription, it's the best-value security camera available. Pair it with Alexa for voice commands and motion alerts.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Buying Guide -->
    <section class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">How to Set Up Your Starter Kit</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Order matters: set up voice control first</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Install the Echo Dot first and set up the Alexa app before adding anything else. Once Alexa is running, every subsequent device you add will be visible to it via automatic device discovery. The Kasa app links to Alexa with one tap; the Sensi links via the Alexa skill. Setting up Alexa first means you'll be controlling everything by voice within minutes of each new device being installed.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Name devices thoughtfully — you'll thank yourself later</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Name devices by location and function: "Living Room Lamp," "Bedroom Fan," "Porch Outlet." Alexa uses these names literally. "Alexa, turn off the living room lamp" only works if the device is named exactly that. Avoid generic names like "Lamp 1" or "Switch 2" — they become impossible to remember when you have 10+ devices.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Set up Alexa routines for the most value</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">The real power of this kit is automation. In the Alexa app under Routines, create: (1) "Good morning" — thermostat to 70°, living room lights to 100% warm white. (2) "Goodnight" — thermostat to 65°, all lights off, porch plug off. (3) Geofencing — set thermostat to eco mode when everyone leaves, restore it on return. These routines work automatically once set up — no ongoing interaction needed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Guides -->
    <section class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Related Guides</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/smart-home/best-smart-home-starter-kit-under-500" class="group block border border-gray-100 rounded-xl p-4 hover:border-green-200 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <p class="text-xs text-green-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">Smart Home</p>
          <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm group-hover:text-green-700 transition-colors">Best Smart Home Starter Kit Under $500 →</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/smart-home/best-smart-home-hub" class="group block border border-gray-100 rounded-xl p-4 hover:border-green-200 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <p class="text-xs text-green-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">Smart Home</p>
          <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm group-hover:text-green-700 transition-colors">Best Smart Home Hub →</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</Layout>
